mirror with a picture on it by using relative directions to other objects in the room. start by locating the dresser, which is positioned on the left side of the frame. move towards the mirror, which is positioned to the right of the dresser. the mirror should be nearby, slightly below the level of the dresser. look for a picture on the mirror to confirm that you have found the correct object.

mirror with a stone wall behind it. start by locating the radiator. the mirror is located to the right and slightly above the radiator. next, find the sink. the mirror is located to the left and slightly below the sink. finally, locate the shelf. the mirror is located to the left and slightly above the shelf.
